body.name: TUTOTAK Small Narrow Side Table with Charging Station, Skinny End Table for Small Spaces, Slim Nightstand with USB Ports and Outlet, Sofa Beside Table with Wheels, Black TB01BK046
deliveryMessages: Or fastest delivery Thursday, February 15. Order within 9 hrs 49 mins
features: [Side Table with Charging Station] This Narrow side table with 1 AC outlet, 2 USB ports, and the 4.9 ft extension cord helps you charge your phone, lamp, or game console at the same time. Keeps you away from wall corner where the home power outlet located.

[2 Ways & Wheels/Adjustable Feet] The small end table provides you with 4 adjustable feet and 4 wheels, and you can choose whether to install wheels. The wheels allow you to move this end table freely. The adjustable feet for you to adjust on uneven floors. It also prevent the metal legs from directly touching the floor. Avoid tiles, Scratches on wooden floors.

[3-Tier Storage for Small Space] Size: 7.9”D x 15.8”W x 23”H or 24.5”H（with wheels）, 7.9” width, this industrial side table is perfect for small spaces as a sofa end table, nightstand put in the corner and small spaces, the beside table not very spacious but still has enough space to add a lamp, photo frame, coffee and magazines in the top panel, and you can charge your phone or tablet by placing it on the second layer board and you also can put storage basket on the bottom board.

[Multi-purpose] The skinny end table can be used as a sofa side table, nightstand, bedside table, small coffee table, reading table, corner table, drink table, snack table, decorative displays table. It's an ideal choice for living room, bedroom, hallway, or office.

[After Sale Service] Simple and Easy to Assemble! Assembly instructions are included in the package, no other special tools are required. Every end table is thoroughly and rigorously tested. TUTOTAK friendly and professional customer service will respond to you within 24 hours. If you have any questions, please feel free to contact us!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 16, 2023
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. It’s a $35 table, I don’t expect it to look like fine furniture. But I really think it looks pretty good for the price, certainly much better than the little cooler I was using for a table! It fits perfectly for the small space by my recliner. I was very pleasantly surprised by how sturdy and wobble free it is. The legs have plastic inserts for you to put screws into and on the bottom the foot pads are adjustable so that you can eliminate any wobble. The only tool needed was a small Phillips head screwdriver and the Allen wrenches that came in the box. It’s very simple to put together. Everything is labeled although the sticker had come off of one of the little bags of screws. The pictures are clear enough that it was easy to determine which screw goes where. You can see in the pictures plastic and metal inserts for the screws to go into. Also an iPad and 8 1/2 x 11 sheet of paper along with recliner for a size comparison. Very happy with this little table and love the fact that it has charging ports on it.

reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Came with broken parts
reviews.reviewText: The small tables themselves are great, wonderful function for what I needed and the construction of both units was not difficult. Gave it 3 out of 5 stars though bc on the second table I built, one of the legs that you have to screw in was broken. It was a giant pain with one already being built to have to undo everything to send it back for a replacement(only option Amazon returns provides), so I ended up doing a “tape and glue job” on the broken piece to get it together, but I wouldn’t exactly label that table as sturdy now lol. Bit disappointing in that for the price,so you do take your chances in buying this set.
